article.headline: Drake 58, E. Michigan 54
article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. -- Drake overcame a 25-point, 10-rebound performance by Brandon Bowdry on Wednesday night to defeat Eastern Michigan 58-54 and snap a three-game losing streak. Seth VanDeest and Rayvonte Rice scored 13 points apiece for the Bulldogs (3-4), and Ryan Wedel added 10. Bowdry was the only player in double figures for the Eagles (1-7), who shot just 35 percent from the field including 3 for 17 on 3-point attempts. Drake led 20-7 midway through the first half before Eastern Michigan rallied to pull within 29-28 at halftime. The Bulldogs increased that lead to as many as nine points in the second half, but the Eagles rallied again, pulling within 54-51 with 1:26 remaining. After a layup by Rice extended the lead to 56-51, Bowdry hit a 3-pointer with 11 seconds left to bring Eastern Michigan within two. Frank Wiseler sealed the win with a pair of free throws for Drake.
